@node "usage" "Using SPYMASTER 2000"

Once all data has been configured...Ready to start....

Select the site you wish to view......Double Click (v1.1)

ABORT = Aborts current download and Exits current loop

STOP  = allows you to continue current download but will
        exit the loop with the download is finished....

PICSAVE  = used to move the file from Ram:T/ to the defined 
        Storage dir if you are using Manual Save..


QUIT = Will abort download & stop program loop and Exit


END = Will Stop the delay and start next download..

BROWSE =  shift-select as many sites as you would like to view in one pass

LOOP =   Shift-select as many sites as you would like to view in a loop

X =  this is emergency exit use in an emergency..........


OK... some hints......

YOU can change sites during the delay...........


@endnode
@node "sites" "Sites for SPYMASTER 2000"

Make sure Spymaster is not working when you go to update sites.....


ADDing, Updating, Deleting Sites for SpyMaster..

To add a site to the sitelist just input the correct data for the picture
page of the approiate site....(Always check the site with a Browser)
then click ADD..(Note!!... the site.list is only saved in memory not HD)

To update a site double click the site and make changes in you need to make
then click UPdate....(Note!!... the site.list is only saved in memory not HD)

Deleting, select site and hit delete.....
(Note!!... the site.list is only saved in memory  not HD)

Saving..... This will save the current list to your HardDrive and reload..

Clear just clears the edit area.........

Load list loads current saved list on the Hard drive....

The site has four parts.... Site Name less than 14 characters, Site Delay
Site Password, Site Address

Enter User:Password this format....

Leave Password blank if site does not need one....

Site Address does not need Http://

Site Delay is the time to wait between downloading pics.....
@endnode


@node "spy" "SPYMASTER 2000"

@{b}SPYMASTER 2000@{ub}

 SPYMASTER is a program which will allow you to download pictures available on 
 the Internet from "real time" web Cameras. As I'm sure you are aware of some 
 other programs that are available, but they didn't do all I wanted then to do.
 So I wrote my own....

 Some features of SPYMASTER:

 Muirexx GUI..

 Able to Use IBrowse/Multiview(w/datatypes)/Visage/Fastview as viewer

 Adjustable Delay between downloads....

 Progress download gauge

 Download is ABORTable

 Text Editable Site.list or from GUI

 Manual or Auto Save

 Ask if you want do download if the same file already exists in Storage path:

 Hide GUI as a AppIcon.....(Quit button in GUI)

@endnode
@node "req" "Requirements"

  @{b}Requirements for Spymaster@{ub}

  Muirexx 3.0a (©Russell Leighton)

  Libs:rexxreqtools.library
  Libs:rexxsupport.library
  
  IBrowse v1.12 

  Multiview v40.8 with Jpeg datatypes....
    
@endnode
@node "install" "Installation"


  @{b}MANUAL INSTALLATION SPYMASTER 2000@{ub}

  Copy SPYMASTER dir anyplace on your harddrive.

  Check for required libs.

  Copy Base64Encoded to C:

  Click on Spymaster Icon, and select Information from Workbench
   Pulldown and enter Muirexx full path with program name

  ***Make sure you are using Muirexx 3.0a....Save****

  Click icon & GUI will open....    

  Mui bubble help is available....

  When the GUI opens you need to configure the program..Click Config page
  
  Viewers... IBrowse/Multiview/User

         IBrowse = will open a IBrowse window on you Workbench and use to 
                   view download pictures...

         Multiview = will open a Window on Workbench and use datatypes to 
                     view download pictures

         User = define any cli based viewer
          
         user Options: define user viewer cli options


  TypeSave ... Auto Save/Manual Save

          Auto Save = will download pictures to the defined Storage dir..

          Manual Save = will download pictures to Ram:t/
                        and will delete current pic at the 
                        start of next download

   Pictures filenames:

          Picture filenames come from the picture info....

          Sitename_Year_mth/day_time.jpg

          ie. Ana_971025_102354.jpg

          file is from Ana's cam, Oct 25 1997, at 10:23:54 GMT

          GMT = Grenwich Mean Time

         
Do Ask/Do Not Ask  = if file exists do you want a requestor to pop up 
                     ask you what to do or Do Not Ask will just download
                     even if files exists.
    
IB on Workbench= IB will open on workbench......
IB on Custom = IB will open on your custom screen if you have defined...


Smart/Full = Smart delay will take the downlaod time and minus it from the 
             actual delay 
             Full will not use the downlaod time, and Full delay time used


   Proxy... fill in you proxy server if you use one.. and check the box 
            for proxy

   Multiview Options = needs at least these options - WINDOW PORT=SPYMASTER

   IBrowse Path:    Full IBrowse path & filename

   Picture Store:   Dir where download pic are to be stored.....

   user Path:     Full path & filename of user viewer
  
   user options:  cli options....

   SAVE config..... you should get a requestor saying Config Saved


@endnode
